Contestants on Netflix’s Too Hot to Handle get close, but not too close.
NetflixWhen Netflix executives decided to greenlight the streaming service’s newest reality TV experiment Too Hot to Handle, they couldn’t have predicted how apt the show’s wild-on-paper premise would be for our current moment.
Lana, Too Hot to Handle’s virtual host, may look like a knockoff lava-lamp Alexa, but she’s the one running the show.
Shows like Too Hot to Handle succeed, when they do succeed, by finding a careful balance between titillation and pathos.
Despite an irresistibly juicy premise, Too Hot to Handle doesn’t know what kind of show it wants to be, and it suffers for lack of direction.